<p>Wednesday 14 August</p>
<p>Dead tired when I came off duty, although only a few cases. Slept all day till 4.30 when I got up &amp; had some tea.</p>
<p>American Field Ambulance arrived just after tea to take over from us. They had just done a stunt a few days before, &amp; now are expecting another on this Sector. This particular Yankee division was in the fighting at Villers Bretoneux when the town was a death trap. As for us we are expecting to leave here today or tomorrow, have about four days' spell &amp; then go into a big stunt for a few days,</p>
